	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Originally, I stored pictures as 1bpp tile screens, as they would appear in a tile editor, but when space got tight, I applied simple RLE compression to them.  This got 2 screens of 1024 bytes each (with a lot of space wasted) down to a total of 900 bytes or (usually) less.  If I made a better scheme to compress the on-off dithering that all the pics use, I could make them even smaller for sure.  But I don't need to, really.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


